Master Answer:
Vaccines are very safe and effective and prevent diseases that can be dangerous, or even deadly. They work with the body's natural defense system to safely develop immunity to disease. They enlist the help of white blood cells to fight infections, produce antibodies and make cells called memory cells, which go into action quickly if the body encounters the same germ again.
